(Test format strings with mixed variables and expressions)

(Mixed interpolation)
a text called "name" is "Alice".
a number called "age" is 25.
a number called "yearz" is 5.
Print "Hello, {name}! You are {age} years old.".
Print "In {yearz} years, {name} will be {age add yearz}.".
Print "{name} is {age} now and will be {age add yearz} then.".

(Complex calculations in format strings)
a number called "width" is 10.
a number called "height" is 5.
a text called "shape" is "rectangle".
a number called "width_squared" is width multiply width.
a number called "height_squared" is height multiply height.
a number called "diagonal_squared" is width_squared add height_squared.
Print "Shape: {shape}".
Print "Area: {width multiply height}".
Print "Perimeter: {2 multiply width add 2 multiply height}".
Print "Diagonal approx: {diagonal_squared}".

(Multiple expressions in one string)
a number called "base" is 100.
a number called "tax" is 8.00.
a number called "discount" is 5.00.
a number called "tax_amount" is base multiply tax divide 100.00.
a number called "total" is base add tax_amount.
a number called "discount_amount" is base multiply discount divide 100.00.
a number called "final_price" is base subtract discount_amount.
Print "Base: ${base}, Tax: ${tax_amount:.2}, Total: ${total:.2}".
Print "With ${discount:.0}% discount: ${final_price:.2}".
